The copy of a letter, sent from two thousand youthfull citizens, to the menacing marshall of the Kings-Bench, Sir John Lenthall.
1 sheet ([1] p.)
March 4. London, Printed by John Raworth, [London] : 1641 [i.e. 1642]
The letter castigates Lenthall for his actions against "Round-head, and self will'd Seperatists". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
